Definition: using the name of one thing for that of another with which it is closely associated
Example: to say `he spent the evening reading Shakespeare' is metonymic because it substitutes the author himself for the author's works
Synonyms: noun, communication, metonym, metonymical, metonymy, using, the, name, of, one, thing, for, that, another, with, which, it, is, closely, associated, to, say, he, spent, evening, reading, Shakespeare, because, substitutes, author, himself, s, works
Category: adj.all
